LasVegas2018 XLE We are opening a Bear Call Credit on the Energy ETF This bear call spreads strategy is to realize a profit by making cash that is a net credit formed by the difference in a SOLD CALL price and a BOUGHT CALL price While the stock goes down the investor keeps the net credit difference in premiums For new members we are including a picture of how the order is entered We are BUYING to OPEN 10 Calls strike 63 price 013 expiring June 14 2019 At the same time we SELLING to OPEN 10 Calls strike 62 price 027 expiring June 14 This gives us a CREDIT of 013 which is 13000 since we are buying 10 contracts equivalent to 1000 shares One contract is 100 shares The actual cost of the trade is 100000 but since we received a Credit of 13000 we are only risking 87000 As long as XLE is below 6200 in 15 days the trade will close automatically and we keep our credit If XLE rises to fast we can close the trade and enter a new strategy
